ence or next to the word \"you\"."}]}, {"id": "02-07", "tn": [{"ref": "", "text": "This is a continuation of Jonah's prayer that started in [[:en:bible:notes:jon:02:01|2:2]]."}, {"ref": "I remembered Yahweh", "text": "Since Jonah was praying to Yahweh, it might be more clear in some languages to say \"I thought about you, Yahweh\"  or \"Yahweh, I thought about you.\" (UDB)"}, {"ref": "then my prayer came to you, to your holy temple", "text": "\"then you in your holy temple heard my prayer\""}, {"ref": "Those who pay attention to useless gods", "text": "\"People who pay attention to useless gods\""}, {"ref": "reject your faithfulness toward themselves", "text": "\"are rejecting you, who would be faithful to them\""}]}, {"id": "02-09", "tn": [{"ref": "", "text": "This is a continuation of Jonah's prayer that started in [[:en:bible:notes:jon:02:01|2:2]]."}, {"ref": "But as for me, I", "text": "This expression in English shows that there is a contrast between the people Jonah had just spoken about and himself. They paid attention to useless gods but he would worship Yahweh. It can also be translated as \"But I.\""}, {"ref": "I will sacrifice to you with a voice of thanksgiving", "text": "This means that Jonah would thank God while he offered a sacrifice to him. It is not clear whether Jonah planned to thank God by singing or shouting joyfully."}, {"ref": "Salvation comes from Yahweh", "text": "\"Salvation\" is a noun. Its meaning can also be expressed with a verb: Yahweh is the one who saves people.\""}, {"ref": "upon the dry land", "text": "\"upon the ground\" or \"onto the shore\""}]}, {"date_modified": "20150514"}]
